    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The extension is noted, but you're misunderstanding the situation. This isn't a matter of 'authorization'—the EOL status is a hardware reality. The wipe is a standard procedure to prevent data corruption on failing drives. Why do you believe a manual review is necessary for a routine migration?",
